That shows a lot of promise. There are several boards on 4chan for you to explore, each has several running general threads you shuold familiarize yourself with and participate in the ones you feel fit what you're going after. Obviously, furry will be restricted to /trash/, but /d/ /co/ /aco/ /ic/ are all good hunting grounds for feedback and practice. Donate time to do edits and draw requests, don't worry about them being perfect or great, but use them to practice and show off & build rep. There are also commission threads when you feel you can compete. Do what you want to do, skip the stuff that doesn't interest you.

You'll need to develop a marketing and promotion strategy. That's complex, so you need to think through carefully what you want to do, what skillz you have and which ones you need. Decide what work you will put your real name on and what work needs a pseudonym. Compartmentalize your extreme fetish work so that it doesn't get associated with your normie work too quickly. Eventually, it will get connected. Hopefully after a few years and your rep is solid and doesn't make a difference.

Your base talent isn't a great concern, although practice every day and always look for improvement no matter how good you get. Working social media to get a rep and a following is the trick. Half-assed artists make bank because they develop a following, not because they are better than you are. With your base talent, you can make more bank than they can with a decent plan.

Start building your following immediately. That's the slow part. It will snowball and accelerate eventually, if you keep your rep high with fans and others in the community. Don't be an asshole. That will suppress your customer base in half a dozen different ways. Study how other artists are successful, and how they communicate with their fanbase.

Good luck!
